    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A colorless, pungent carboxylic acid which polymerizes in the presence of oxygen. Acrylic acid is used in the manufacture of acrylic resins, plastics, fibers, and coatings. Acrylic acid was first synthesized in 1843. Formula is formula CH2=CHCOOH</Note_Text>
